President Biden has announced his intention to appoint several individuals to key roles in the Board for International Food and Agricultural Development (BIFAD) and the U.S. Commission for the Preservation of America's Heritage Abroad. Laurence B. Alexander, the Chancellor of the University of Arkansas at Pine Bluff, will serve as the Chair of BIFAD. Other members include Pamela K. Anderson, the former Director General of the International Potato Center, Marie Boyd, an associate professor at the University of South Carolina School of Law, Rattan Lal, a Distinguished University Professor of Soil Science at The Ohio State University, Lenis Saweda O. Liverpool-Tasie, an associate professor at Michigan State University, Henri G. Moore, the Vice President/Head of Responsible Business at GSK Consumer Health, Kathy Spahn, the President and CEO of Helen Keller Intl, Starlet "Star" Jones Lugo, an attorney and TV host, G. Jonathan Greenwald, a former U.S. diplomat, Nicole Mavis Isaac, a leader at Meta, Nancy K. Kaufman, a former CEO of National Council of Jewish Women, Michael T. Marquardt, the Chair of the Board of Directors of the American Cancer Society, Maureen Catherine Pikarski, a partner at Gordon & Pikarski law firm, and William H. Shaheen, a former U.S. Attorney and District Court Judge.